cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SY

This paper deals with improving predictive uncertainty estimation in computer vision tasks, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of Dropout regularization and deep neural networks points towards cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the focus on computer vision tasks suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of Bayesian inference and Hamiltonian Monte Carlo suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the potential application of the proposed method to autonomous driving systems suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control).
